\ie
\c 1
\s1 Koresh returns some Jews
\p
\v 1 In the first year that Koresh \add (Cyrus)\add* was king of Persia \add (Heb. Paras)\add*, Yahweh stirred up \add his\add* spirit in order to fulfil what \add he’d\add* spoken through the prophet Yirmeyah \add (Jeremiah)\add*.\x + \xo 1:1: \xt Jer 25:11; 29:10.\x* \add So\add* \add the king\add* distributed a written proclamation throughout his kingdom, saying,
\v 2 “Koresh, king of Persia, declares this: Yahweh, the god of heaven, has given me all the kingdoms in the world, and he’s appointed me to build a residence for him in Yerushalem in Yehudah.\x + \xo 1:2: \xt Isa 44:28.\x*
\v 3 Anyone among you who’s one of his followers is free to go to Yerushalem (in Yehudah) \add to help\add* build a temple there for Israel’s God Yahweh—the god of Yerushalem. May God go with you.
\v 4 Those who live near these people but who’re not going themselves, should donate gold and silver, and goods and livestock, plus cash as a voluntary offering for God’s temple in Yerushalem.
\p
\v 5 Then \add some\add* of the leaders of Benyamin and Yehudah, and \add some\add* priests and Levites—all of whom had had their spirits stirred up by God—left to go and build Yahweh’s residence in Yerushalem.
\v 6 Their neighbours had helped them by \add donating\add* gold and silver utensils, goods and livestock, and expensive gifts, as well as the voluntary offerings of cash.
\p
\v 7 Then King Koresh brought out the equipment from Yahweh’s temple that Nevukadnetstsar \add (Nebuchadnezzar)\add* had brought \add all the way\add* from Yerushalem and had put in the house of his gods.
\v 8 \add He\add* \add put the treasurer Mitedat in charge of bringing them out\add* and Sheshbatstsar, the ruler of Yehudah, \add in charge of accepting them and listing them\add*.
\v 9 There were: thirty gold basins, one thousand silver basins, twenty-nine knives,
\v 10 thirty gold bowls, 410 silver bowls, and a thousand other utensils,
\v 11 \add coming to a total of 5,400 gold and silver utensils\add*. Sheshbatstsar \add took all of that with the group\add* of exiles going from Babylon to Yerushalem.
\c 2
