\r (Neh. 7:4-73)
\p
\v 1 Out of the captives that Babylonian King Nevukadnetstsar \add (Nebuchadnezzar)\add* had brought \add as slaves\add* to Babylon, these are \add their descendants\add* who returned to Yerushalem in Yehudah—\add each person returning to their own ancestral town\add*.
\v 2 The ones who went with Zerubbabel were: Yeshua, Nehemyah, Serayah, Re’elayah, Mordecai, Bilshan, Mispar, Bigvai, Rehum, and Ba’anah.
\p Their numbers were:
